{:title "Usage Tracking & Provider Metrics"
 :description "Detailed usage tracking and rate-limit metrics for both virtual models and individual providers."
 :acceptance-criteria
 ["Each successful LLM call increments token usage for the specific provider used"
  "Rate-limit failures increment a 'rate-limits' counter for the failed provider"
  "Virtual model success results propagate the actual provider identity to the top level"
  "Audit logs include the :provider field for successful completions"
  "The /api/v1/stats and /stats endpoints include provider-level breakdown"
  "Documentation (README.md, AGENTS.md) reflects the new observability capabilities"
  "Tool outputs are sanitized to prevent structural role-injection"]
 :data-model
 {:usage-stats
  {"model-or-provider-id"
   {:requests 0
    :total-input-tokens 0
    :total-output-tokens 0
    :total-tokens 0
    :rate-limits 0
    :context-overflows 0
    :last-updated 0}}}
 :edge-cases
 ["What if the provider identity is unknown? (Fall back to model name)"
  "Does tracking usage for a virtual model (e.g., 'brain') still work alongside the provider track? (Yes, track both)"
  "Max-iterations reached: should we skip usage recording or record with zero tokens?"
  "Tool denied (policy): should we record a denied attempt? (Future enhancement)"]
 :follow-up
 {:test-llm-default-usage "Make default usage nil in test-llm-server to force explicit opt-in for usage-aware tests"
  :policy-error-fingerprinting "Return generic 'Tool execution denied' from execute-tool instead of specific policy reason to prevent probing"}}
